<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belarusian Leaders Meet Chinese Vice Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MINSK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Belarusian leaders today held talks
on bilateral relations with Chinese Vice Premier Wu Bangguo who
arrived last night for an official visit.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with the Chinese official this morning,
Belarusian President Alexander Lukashenko said that Belarus highly
values relations with China and regards it as a sincere friend.
</P>
<P>
Lukashenko said that developing a friendly relationship with
China is not only in the interests of the two countries but also
conducive to world peace.
</P>
<P>
He said Belarus and China should cooperate more effectively in
the fields of politics, economy and science and technology as well
as international affairs.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese vice premier briefed Lukashenko on China's foreign
policy and its relations with other countries. He said that both
Belarus and China oppose any countries imposing their own will and
model on others and hold that every country should have the right
to choose their own road of development.
</P>
<P>
Wu said that by signing political documents with his Chinese
counterpart Jiang Zemin during his visit to China last year,
Lukashenko has promoted Sino-Belarusian ties to a new level and
laid the legal foundation for further improvement.
</P>
<P>
Also on Thursday morning, Belarusian Prime Minister Sergei Ling
told the Chinese official that Belarus is satisfied with its
relations with China and hopes to strengthen cooperation in the
fields of auto industry, chemical industry, science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Wu told his host that China is willing to explore new ways and
areas for cooperation with Belarus under the conditions of their
market economies and is encouraging Chinese enterprises to
establish direct economic and trade links with their Belarusian
counterparts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
