<HEADLINE> Russian Helicopter Crash Kills Five </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 3 (Xinhua) -- All five people on board a Russian
helicopter died today when it crashed into the Ural mountains in
central Russia, Itar-Tass News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The M-8 helicopter was ferrying two doctors to a mine which
called for medical help when it collided with a radio tower due to
heavy snowstorm, the report said. 
</P>
