<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belarusian FM Hails Belarus-Russia Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Belarusian Foreign Minister Ivan
Antonovich hailed the creation of the Belarus-Russia Union as a
very important step in the integration of the two countries as
well as all Europe.
</P>
<P>
Antonovich told a news conference that both Belarus and Russia
intend to realize the union within the framework of all-European
integration, the Itar-Tass News Agency reported from Minsk.
</P>
<P>
The treaty forming the Union was signed by Presidents Boris
Yeltsin of Russia and Alexander Lukashenko of Belarus on Wednesday
in Moscow.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also signed a wide-ranging charter which would
be submitted for public discussion till May 15.
</P>
<P>
When asked how a nationwide discussion of the draft Charter of
the Union would proceed, Antonovich said all remarks, proposals
and addenda are to be referred to a special commission.
</P>
<P>
Besides, the Belarusian Foreign Ministry will hold a seminar on
the foreign policy aspects of the draft Charter, the minister
said, affirming that the nationwide discussion will result in a
final version of the Charter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
