<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Accepts U.N. Chief's Clarification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini today said that United Nations Secretary-General Kofi Annan
had cleared up a statement which ruffled Italian feathers on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In his earlier statement, Annan said Italy needed to make
"psychological reparation" for last Friday's tragic shipwreck of
Albanians before going in to lead a multinational aid protection
force.
</P>
<P>
Dini reacted sharply on Wednesday, saying Albania, not Italy,
might be expected to compensate for the wave of immigrants Italy
has had to cope with.
</P>
<P>
But today Dini said Annan had explained his meaning
"better": that Italy must do everything needed to make sure the
aid operation runs smoothly.
</P>
<P>
Dini said he shared these views and added that Italy would also
do everything in its power to assist Albania regarding the
shipwreck itself. 
</P>
</TEXT>
