<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Host African Oil Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 3 (Xinhua) -- An African oil trade conference is
to be held in Harare from April 14 to 17 with an aim of outlining
opportunities in the deregulated oil market.
</P>
<P>
The conference, organized by the Eastern and Southern African
Trade and Development Bank, would identify new business
opportunities in Africa, particularly the Common Market for East
and Southern Africa (COMESA) sub-region, for those committed to
the different aspects of the oil trade exploration, extraction,
trading and financing.
</P>
<P>
The organizer said here today the conference would benefit
those in shipping, insurance, storage, refining and marketing as
well as the provision of port facilities, pipelines and ancillary
equipment. 
