<HEADLINE> Submarine Cable Among Syria, Egypt and Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The optical submarine cable
connecting Syria, Egypt and Lebanon was completed today at Syria's
western coastal town of Tartus, the Syrian Arab News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The submarine cable between Syria and Egypt is 750 kilometers
long and between Syria and Lebanon, 130 kilometers. Circuits with
Egypt is expected to increase from the current 30,000 telephone
circuits to 60,000, while circuits with Lebanon will stand at
7,600.
</P>
<P>
The 28-million-U.S.-dollar project, which was completed in 13
months, is part of a regional Arab network that is complementary
to an international network extending from Southeast Asia to
Europe and America.
</P>
<P>
It will have far reaching economic significance besides ensuring
telephone linkage among Syria, Egypt and Lebanon and the rest of
the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
