<DOCNO> XIE19970404.0014 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Soccer Squad Named Asian Women Team of Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese national women's
soccer team was named Asian Women's Team of the Year for 1996 by
the Asian Football Confederation (AFC) here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Its coach Ma Yunan, who guided the team to win the silver medal
at the 1996 Atlanta Olympic Games in the United States, was also
selected Asian Coach of the Year by a AFC panel.
</P>
<P>
Iranian striker Khodadad Azizi was named Asian Player of the
Year while Iran also received the 1996 Fair Play Award.
</P>
<P>
Azizi, 25, was chosen for his outstanding performance and role
in helping Iran finish third at the Asian Cup tournament held in
the United Arab Emirates last December, the AFC said.
</P>
<P>
Azizi, the Most Valuable Player in the Asian Cup, beat other
finalists for the honor, including his compatriot Ali Daei, South
Korea's Ko Jeong-woon, and Saudi Arabia players Mohamed Al Daeyea
and Yousef Al Thuniyan.
</P>
<P>
Thailand's Bamrong Boonprom was named Young Player of the Year,
Saudi Arabia was voted National Men's Team of the Year, and South
Korea's Ilhwa Chunma was named Club of the Year.
</P>
<P>
Pirom Un Prasert of Thailand was voted Referee of the Year, Al
Muwasi Mohamed Hamed of Oman Assistant Referee of the year, and
Azam Mahmoon of Bangladesh Sportswriter of the Year.
</P>
<P>
The awarding ceremony was attended by International Football
Federation President Joao Havelange and General Secretary Sepp
Blatter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
