<HEADLINE> Tour de France in 1998 to Start in Dublin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Next year's Tour de France cycling
race will begin with a sprint through the streets of Dublin in
Ireland next year, officials said in Dublin on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first time that the renowned competition is
launched outside the European mainland.
</P>
<P>
The tour will start with a 7-kilometer timed prologue trial
around Dublin on July 11, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Riders will move to Irish countryside on the second day, when
they have to ascend the Wicklow Hills along the east coast in a
175-kilometer leg which finishes in Dublin's Phoenix Park.
</P>
<P>
Cyclists will have an easier 200-kilometer ride from
Enniscorthy, County Wexford to Cork city on the third day.
</P>
</TEXT>
