<HEADLINE> Riis, Zuelle, Jalabert to Miss Giro d'Italia Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Tour de France winner Bjarne Riis of
Denmark, world number one Alex Zuelle of Switzerland and Laurent
Jalabert of France look set to miss this year's Giro d'Italia
cycle race.
</P>
<P>
Reuter reported on Thursday that Riis's Telekom team and the
Once squad for which both Zuelle and world number two Jalabert
ride had turned down the invitation to take part in the 3,885-km
race.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the Giro said the organisers had not yet
been notified who would take part in the race, which starts in
Venice on May 18 and ends on June 8. 
