<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forum to Mark 7th Anniversary of HK SAR Basic Law (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A forum was held in the Great Hall
of the People here today to mark the 7th anniversary of the
promulgation of the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
The participants, who are from the various circles of the
Chinese capital, agreed that the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR is
of historical and international significance.
</P>
<P>
Also, they said that today's meeting is very important for the
publicity and implementation of the Basic Law as well as for Hong
Kong's smooth transition and its stability and prosperity.
</P>
<P>
They pledged to handle matters concerning Hong Kong according
to the Basic Law, in order to make Deng Xiaoping's concept of "one
country, two systems" come true in the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
Lei Jieqiong, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, presided over the forum.
</P>
<P>
Among those attending and addressing the gathering were Wang
Hanbin, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress; Zeng Jianhui, director of the Information
Office of the State Council; Zhou Nan, director of the Xinhua News
Agency Hong Kong Branch; Chen Ziying, deputy director of the Hong
Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the State Council; and Wu
Jianfan, a member of the former Committee for Drafting the Basic
Law of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
Wan Hanbin said the Basic Law, which has made the "one country,
two systems" concept into law, stipulates the basic system and
policy of the Hong Kong SAR.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, it outlines a clear blueprint for the future of Hong
Kong, and turned the concept of "one country, two systems" into a
series of concrete provisions in the law, he said, adding that the
Basic Law will provide a legal guarantee for the successful
implementation of the "one country, two systems" concept.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
