<HEADLINE> France Welcomes Nomination of Tshisekedi as Zairean PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 3 (Xinhua) -- France today welcomed the nomination
by Zairean President Mobutu Sese Seko of Etienne Tshisekedi as the
country's prime minister, saying it should create a "favorable
condition" for the two warring sides of Zaire to start talks this
weekend in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
"We have taken note of the nomination of Tshisekedi as the new
chief of the Zairean government. This nomination should create a
favorable climate for the inter-Zairean negotiations which should
open at the end of the week in South Africa," said French Foreign
Ministry spokesman Yves Doutriaux.
</P>
<P>
The negotiations will be held through the mediation of Mohammed
Sahnoun, the envoy of the United Nations and the Organization of
African Unity for the Great Lakes region in central Africa.
</P>
<P>
On the plight of the refugees and displaced people in Zaire,
the spokesman said that their situation remains "very worrying."
</P>
<P>
"We are doing our utmost to appeal to the international
community, especially to the humanitarian organizations and our
Western partners, in order that a solution be found and that one
can save the people in distress when it is still not too late,"
said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He said that a French Foreign Ministry official in charge of
African affairs had discussed the issue with a U.S. State
Department official in Paris Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
