<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Thai Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today told the visiting Thai Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh
that China and Thailand can develop long-term, good-neighborly and
all-round cooperative relations marked by mutual trust and a view
to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said Sino-Thai friendship has set a fine example for the
peaceful co-existence between countries with different systems,
adding that his meeting with Chavalit is like that between old
friends who have been reunited.
</P>
<P>
He said he was convinced that Chavalit's current China visit
will further the development of bilateral friendly and cooperative
relations.
</P>
<P>
China and Thailand have enjoyed time-honored friendship, and
they have always been good friends and neighbors, Jiang said,
noting that although the international situation has changed
greatly since the two countries forged diplomatic relations, they
have always trusted and understood each other and had a sincere
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Friendship between the people of the two countries has
increased, he said, and they have made progress in many areas.
</P>
<P>
"This proves that countries with diverse systems should and can
achieve peaceful co-existence and common development," Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
Chavalit said the number of government ministers, military
leaders and enterpreneurs who accompanied him on his China trip
set an unprecedented record, and symbolizes the deep friendship
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said he can see great changes that have taken place in China
every time he comes to the country.
</P>
<P>
"The Thai people are pleased with this," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Thai government will continue to devote itself
to promoting Thai-Chinese friendship, and adhere to the "one
China" policy.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president said that the two countries belong to
Asia, the Chinese government has always attached great importance
on advancing its friendly ties with Thailand, and they have a good
basis for bilateral cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"China is willing to consolidate and foster bilateral
good-neighborly relations at the dawn of the next century, to
raise such ties to a new high," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Citing 1997 as important in Chinese history, he said China will
witness two major events this year: the forthcoming 15th National
Congress of the Chinese Communist Party, which will follow the
concept of building socialism with Chinese characteristics in
order to push forward the opening up and socialist modernization
drive into the 21st century; and the China's resumption of
exercising its sovereignty over Hong Kong, which will bring it a
more prosperous and stable future according to the policies of
"one country, two systems", "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong"
and "high degree of autonomy".
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's return to the motherland is the first step to the
completion of China's peaceful reunification, which will be
followed by Macao's stable transition and the solving of the
Taiwan issue," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
He noted China's reunification complies with desire of the
people and the historical trend, saying that splitting the
motherland will be in vain.
</P>
<P>
A stable, developing and powerful China will be a major
contribution to peace and development in the Asia-Pacific region,
as well as in the world at large, he said.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his thanks to Chavalit and the Thai
government for their adhering to the "one China" stance and
supporting China's reunification.
</P>
<P>
Chavalit said the Thai government and people are fully
confident in China's development.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China's smooth resumption of the exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong is a source of pride for the Chinese
people as well for all Asians.
</P>
<P>
A unified and powerful China is an important strength for
safeguarding world peace, he said, and the unwarranted charges
against China by some people are completely erroneous. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970404.0024 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forum to Mark 7th Anniversary of HK SAR Basic Law (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wang said that the Basic Law has displayed increasing vitality
and importance as it relates to Hong Kong's stability and
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the belief that the law will play a crucial role
for the region's long-term prosperity and stability after China
resumes the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1.
Also, it will have a far-reaching impact on China's cause of
reunification in general, he added.
</P>
<P>
Wang said that in carrying out the Basic Law, all matters
should be handled in strict accordance with it.
</P>
<P>
And, it is of utmost importance to ensure the realization of
the principles of "one country, two systems," "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong" and a high-degree of autonomy, so as to
guarantee the Hong Kong SAR will enjoy the executive, legislative
and independent judicial power and power of final appeal,
according to Wang.
</P>
<P>
Matters within the autonomy of the SAR should be administered
by the SAR on its own, and anything that is up to the Hong Kong
people to decide will be decided by them alone, without any
interference of the central government, Wang said.
</P>
<P>
He said that for a comprehensive implementation of the Basic
Law, no hasty revisions should be made of it.
</P>
<P>
The Basic Law stipulates that the socialist system and policies
shall not be practiced in the Hong Kong SAR, and the existing
capitalist system and way of life there will remain unchanged for
50 years, Wang reiterated.
</P>
<P>
The law also says that "no amendment to this law shall
contravene the established basic policies of the People's Republic
of China regarding Hong Kong," he said.
</P>
<P>
This, he said, shows that the basic policies of the People's
Republic of China regarding Hong Kong set in the Sino-British
Joint Declaration have been contained in the Basic Law, which
cannot be revised within 50 years, Wang noted.
</P>
<P>
Wang stressed that strict implementation of the Basic Law is
highly important for Hong Kong's continued success in the next 50
years.
</P>
<P>
With the guarantee of the Basic Law, and with the efforts of
the Hong Kong compatriots and the support of all the Chinese
people, Hong Kong will surely have an even brighter future after
its return to the motherland, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970404.0025 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forum to Mark 7th Anniversary of HK SAR Basic Law (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zeng Jianhui said that the Chinese government promised in the
Sino-British Joint Declaration to guarantee Hong Kong residents'
freedom of speech and publication.
</P>
<P>
During the drafting of the Basic Law, Zeng said, ensuring Hong
Kong residents' freedom of the press was included at the request
of the press circles in the region. This clearly shows that the
Basic Law specially guarantees freedom of the press, he pointed
out.
</P>
<P>
According to the Basic Law, after Hong Kong returns to the
motherland on July 1, 1997, freedom of the press in Hong Kong will
be fully guaranteed by law.
</P>
<P>
Zeng stressed that the information departments and institutions
between the Chinese mainland and Hong Kong will not be
subordinated to each other or interfere in each other's affairs.
</P>
<P>
The management method of the Chinese mainland media shall not
be used in Hong Kong and Hong Kong will act in accordance with its
original system and rules of operation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Nan said since the promulgation of the Basic Law, various
social organizations, newspapers and people in the various circles
of Hong Kong have done a great deal to promote the Basic Law,
which has had a positive influence on society.
</P>
<P>
He summarized the work to promote the Basic Law as follows:
</P>
<P>
-- large-scale activities have been held to mark the
anniversary of the promulgation of the Basic Law;
</P>
<P>
-- a rich variety of public activities have been conducted to
introduce the Basic Law throughout the year;
</P>
<P>
-- a batch of supplementary books have been published about the
Basic Law to help clarify issues for Hong Kong people;
</P>
<P>
-- activities have been held that included the related
departments of the inland areas to expand the influence of the
Basic Law;
</P>
<P>
-- more and more Hong Kong people have conscientiously studied
the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Zhou said the majority of Hong Kong residents and the
international community firmly uphold the Basic Law in the various
activities of preparing the Hong Kong SAR in recent years.
</P>
<P>
In dealing with matters in strict accordance with the Basic
Law, they have come to realize that the Chinese government has a
serious attitude toward the implementation of the Basic Law, and
believe that the Basic Law is sure to be carried out to the
letter, he noted.
</P>
</TEXT>
