<DOCNO> XIE19970404.0026 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Forum to Mark 7th Anniversary of HK SAR Basic Law (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chen Ziying said it is seven years since the promulgation of the
Basic Law, and Hong Kong has entered its late-transitional period.
</P>
<P>
"We strictly abide by the Sino-British Joint Declaration, and
firmly upheld the principle that Hong Kong's development in
politics, economy, society and other fields must be in line with
the Basic Law," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Facts prove that only if China and Britain strictly abide by
the Joint Declaration and principles in line with the Basic Law,
will both sides enjoy smooth cooperation on the Hong Kong
question, and Hong Kong will be stable in the transitional period,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Chen said sticking to the Basic Law is a fundamental practice
in preparing the Hong Kong SAR, adding that implementation of the
law also needs to be combined with the characteristics of Hong
Kong, in order to respect its history and actual situation, and to
settle matters concerning the basic interests of the local
residents with a realistic approach.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that although the Basic Law is about the Hong
Kong SAR, it is also a national law, which must be abided by not
only by the Hong Kong residents, but also by the people in the
inland areas, either in the Hong Kong SAR, or in the provinces,
autonomous regions and municipalities of the Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
He also corrected the misunderstanding of some people that they
will be free to go to Hong Kong and establish an organ there
after July 1, 1997, saying that these ideas run counter to the
Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
Wu Jianfan said it is of highest importance to adopt a
practical and effective measure to ensure the Basic Law will be
carried out successfully.
</P>
<P>
The law-enforcement departments must attach great importance to
the implementation of the Basic Law, supervising the carrying out
of the law and solving the legal matters during the process in
time, he noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
