<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Ministry of
Agriculture announced today that over 2.2 million pack animals
have been given preventive inoculation against rinderpest during
the past eight months.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Sileshi Zewde, senior veterinarian from the ministry said
the inoculation was given in parts of Afar and southwestern areas
of the country where rinderpest prevails.
