<HEADLINE> Angola Implements Self-Employment Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Some 1,820 people in Angola's
Luanda Province have got jobs in 640 small enterprises since
November l995, when the Ministry of Public Administration and
Employment began to implement a self-employment program.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed to the press by Venceslau de Matos, an
official in the ministry, here today.
</P>
<P>
He said, the self-employment program is aimed at solving the
problem of unemployment in the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
Under the program, the ministry provides tools to the
jobless people and allows them to run small enterprises to
employ themselves.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has provided 791 sets of tools to the jobless in
the province since November l995, he said.
</P>
<P>
The receivers of the tools must pay 75 percent of the tools'
cost in three and a half years after they start their business,
according to the program.
</P>
<P>
Matos said his ministry will provide raw materials and
equipment to the jobless in the near future to further solve
the problem of unemployment. enditem

