business community at the Hotel Agip in the city, said he was sure
that within 10 to 20 years there would be enough Kiswahili speakers
in Uganda.
</P>
<P>
"We are looking forward to that while we wait the EAC to mature,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
Although the three EAC member states -- Tanzania, Kenya and
Uganda -- had announced Kiswahili as a national language since
independence, the development of the lauguage is quite different
in the three countries.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan prime minister evoked laughter when he cracked a joke
from Uganda that they say Kiswahili was born in Zanzibar, grew up in
Tanganyika, died in Kenya and buried in Uganda and that his ghost is
in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
Musoke, who was flanked by his Tanzanian counterpart Frederick
Sumaye, said the language and other bilateral efforts in enhancing the
co-operation were crucial.
</P>
<P>
He reiterated the need to ensure an ever lasting unity among
the three East African states with a view to strenghening and
sustaining the region's internal and external economy.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister said Kenya, Uganda and Tanzania should form
an economic intergration, saying it was the only way forward to
rapid progress. enditem

