the French defense electronics company Thomson-CSF which is due to
be privatized next month by the French government.
</P>
<P>
The diversified British defense industrial group last Friday
submitted its surprise 1.2 billion-pound (about 2 billion U.S.
dollar) offer for Thomson-CSF to the French government, according
to local press reports today.
</P>
<P>
The French conglomerate Alcatel and Lagarere Group are expected
to have submitted separate bids for acquiring the 58 percent
Thomson stake.
</P>
<P>
Defense analysts in London said that GEC's chances of winning
the bidding were slim as the French government has made it clear
that non-French groups were welcome only as subordinates.
</P>
<P>
The French government is likely to announce later this week
which company will be the final bidder for the Thomson-CSF with
final bids due in by May 7.
</P>
<P>
The outcome of the Thomson privatization is seen as crucial to
the restructuring of the European defense industry, which is under
growing pressure from American defense industry giants, defense
analysts said. 
