<HEADLINE> London Exchange Trades Record in First Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The London International Financial
Futures and Options Exchange (LIFFE) traded a record of 51 million
futures and options contracts in the first quarter of this year,
an increase of 10 percent over the same 1996 period.
</P>
<P>
LIFFE, Europe's leading futures and options exchange and the
third largest exchange of its type in the world, traded 16.57
million contracts in March, a rise of 18 percent on the same month
of last year. Average daily volume amounted to 872,000 futures and
options contracts, representing a daily nominal turnover of 187
billion pounds (306 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Exchange launched the first Euro contract in March. If the
Economic and Monetary Union takes place on schedule in 1999, LIFFE
said, this will convert to a Euro contract. In launching this,
LIFFE has confirmed its leadership in European money market
instruments. It now has 81 percent market share of European
short-term interest rate futures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
