<HEADLINE> EU President Calls for Solution to Turkish-Greek </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Term President of the European
Union (EU) and Dutch Foreign Minister Hans Van Mierlo said here
today that Turkey and Greece should find a solution to the issues
of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Following his two-hour official talks with his Turkish
counterpart Tansu Ciller, Van Mierlo told a joint press conference
that he hoped that Turkish and Greek foreign ministers should meet
during the ministerial Malta EU-Mediterranean Cooperation
Conference scheduled for April 15-16.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Greece are troubled by the Cyprus issue and the
rights of the possession of the islands in the Aegean Sea.
</P>
<P>
For her part, Ciller said that she was very satisfied with Van
Mierlo's attitude towards Turkey's bid for the full EU membership.
</P>
<P>
Van Mierlo said that Turkey's application for the EU entry is
equal with other candidates'.
</P>
<P>
Turkey was greatly angered by a March 4 statement by the EU
Christian Democrats who called Turkey's membership application
unacceptable due to its religious culture.
</P>
<P>
Van Mierlo left Turkey this evening after a several-hour
visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
