<HEADLINE> Egypt, China Explore Cooperation Potentials in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Egypt and China have great potential
for scientific and technological cooperation in the agricultural
field, Egyptian Deputy Prime Minister and Agricultural Minister
Youssef Wali said here today.
</P>
<P>
Wali made the remarks during a meeting with Zhu Lilan, visiting
executive vice-chairperson of the State Science and Technology
Commission of China (SSTC), who is leading a Chinese delegation
for a five-day visit to Egypt since March 29 to boost scientific
and technological ties.
</P>
<P>
Highlighting the two countries' potential in the agricultural
field, Wali said that Egypt and China should work together in the
application of scientific and technological know-how to the
development of the rural areas.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that scientific research, technological
transfer and exchange of information between the two sides will
be furthered.
</P>
<P>
Zhu, in her part, expressed China's readiness to expand
scientific and technological cooperation with Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Under an agreement signed later between the two countries, China
will donate 30 sets of "Great Wall" personal computers and
relevant facilities to the Egyptian Ministry of State for
Scientific Research.
</P>
<P>
During Zhu's talks with Egyptian officials Wednesday, the two
sides agreed to consider a string of projects for future
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
They discussed cooperation in pollution treatment of the Nile
River water, seaweed culture and protein extraction, and the
technology for gold extraction from low quality ores.
</P>
<P>
They also explored the opportunity for further joint work in
the study of desertification phenomenon and sand dune
encroachment, development of rural areas and appropriate
environmental technology. 
</P>
</TEXT>
