of business and trade links between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Sharif also briefed Fischer about the main points of the
agricultural package and tariff reforms announced by his
government recently.
</P>
<P>
Fischer said Australia wanted to increase trade with Pakistan
and was eager for a bilateral agreement with Pakistan on promotion
and protection of investment.
</P>
<P>
Australia was also willing to cooperate in agriculture, dairy
products and mining which were highly developed sectors in
Australia, he added.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, Chaudhry Nisar Ali Khan, Pakistan's
Minister for Petroleum and Natural Resources and Water and Power,
had a meeting with Fischer and the two discussed bilateral
economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan and Australia signed today an agreement on oil and gas
exploration. Australia's Broken Hill Proprietary Petroleum will
undertake oil and gas exploration activities in Pakistan's Sindh
and Balochistan provinces with a minimum financial commitment of
600,000 U.S. dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
