<HEADLINE> Three Contracts Awarded for HK'S New Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Airport Authority (AA) of
Hong Kong has awarded three new contracts relating to Hong Kong's
new airport at Check Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
Two of the contracts relate to the Passenger Terminal Building.
Bringtons Ltd, a British carpet manufacturer, has won a 9.8
million US dollar contract to design, manufacture, supply and
install about 103,000 square meters of broadloom carpet to public
areas, fixed link bridges and aircraft loading bridges.
</P>
<P>
The main body of works will be carried out from November 1997
to February 1998 and the contractor will remain responsible for
care of the works until airport opening in April 1998.
</P>
<P>
The AA will also pay 1.1 million US dollars for an additional
18,000 square meters of the same carpet to be installed in due
course in the northwest concourse.
</P>
<P>
Wilkhahn, Wilkening and Hahne GmbH of Germany has been awarded
a 5.9 million US dollar contract to design, manufacture, supply
and install seating in the terminal's public areas.
</P>
<P>
The total number of seats is about 12,500 and the works are due
 to be completed by the end of February 1998. The contractor will
 be responsible for their care until airport opening.
</P>
<P>
R&AMP;M Warme-Schallschutz and Industrieservice GmbH of Germany has
won a 8.1 million US dollar contract to design, manufacture and
erect jet blast screens and an engine run-up facility.  
</P>
</TEXT>
