<HEADLINE> Shanghai to Recruit More Overseas Talents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China's largest industrial city of
Shanghai will work to annually recruit 20,000 talented personnel
from overseas, sources said at the ongoing three-day international
seminar on 21st Century and Personnel Training.
</P>
<P>
The city will focus its efforts on those Chinese who are
studying abroad and well-educated foreign experts. More than 60
experts from home and overseas are attending the seminar, voicing
their views and offering suggestions on how the city can learn
from foreign experience in making the most of people's talents at
the turn of the century.
</P>
<P>
The city plans to set up talent-development funding, which will
be used to finance overseas experts, foreign talent recruitment,
those who go and study abroad, and young scientists involved in
key research projects.
</P>
<P>
The seminar is sponsored by the Shanghai Public Administration
and Manpower Resources Institute, and East China Teachers'
University. 
</P>
