<HEADLINE> Libyan Foreign Secretary Visits Malta </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Libyan Secretary for Foreign Liaison
and International Cooperation Omar Mustafa Al Muntasser is
visiting Malta today for talks with Prime Minister Alfred Sant.
</P>
<P>
It is the first high level meeting between the two countries
since the Labor Party in Malta assumed power last October.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here say that Muntasser will also hold talks
with Maltese Deputy Premier and Foreign Minister George Vella.
</P>
<P>
The meetings are taking place one week before the convocation
of the second Euro-Mediterranean conference at foreign ministerial
level on October 15 and 16 in the Maltese capital city of
Valletta.
</P>
<P>
It is scheduled that foreign ministers of EU countries as well
as the Arab states on the southern coast of the Mediterranean will
participate in the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The Maltese Prime Minister said last week that Malta regretted
Libya was not invited to the conference. However, he did not
clarify what to do to placate Tripoli.
</P>
<P>
It is unclear if the issue would be brought up at the meetings
between the two countries' officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
