<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Taikang Insurance Company Bids for More Market Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Taikang Life Insurance Co., Ltd, a
newly-created Chinese insurer headquartered in Beijing, will open
four branch companies in Shanghai, Guangzhou, Chongqing and
Shenyang within the year.
</P>
<P>
The fledgling company aims to seize more shares of the booming
life insurance market of China, and to compete with other life
insurance companies, said Zhong Min, a senior official of the
insurance company.
</P>
<P>
She said that the company generated a total of 150 million yuan
in premium income after four months' operation since it was
permitted to start businesses last year. And the figure has
continued to rise, ever since the beginning of this year, she
added.
</P>
<P>
According to the regulations of the People's Bank of China, the
central bank, newly-built nationwide insurance companies can open
a branch in other Chinese cities when their premium income has
increased by 100 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The company's income will exceed at least 400 million yuan this
year, Zhong said.
</P>
<P>
But the total income generated from China's life insurance
market has long remained about 0.3 percent of the country's gross
national product, and average per capita spending on life
insurance services by Chinese people was no more than 1.4 US
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that the total output of China's life insurance
industry will reach 120 billion yuan by the year 2000, however,
there are still a lot of Chinese people who don't know much about
life insurance.
</P>
<P>
So far, there are five major players in China's life insurance
market, namely PICC Life, the Pacific Ocean Insurance Company,
Ping'an Insurance Company, New China Life Insurance Co., Ltd, and
Taikang.
</P>
<P>
Official sources say that the number of Chinese insurance
companies will increase sharply in the coming year, and Chinese
people will benefit from fierce competition among the Chinese
insurers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
