<HEADLINE> Thailand Vows to Curb Laotian Dissidents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Thailand has reassured Laos that
it would not allow Laotian rightist dissidents to use Thailand as
a base to stage subversive activities against the Laotian
government, the Thai news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Thai Interior Minister Sanoh Thiengthong made this pledge on
Thursday at the end of a two-day meeting of governors of the two
countries' border provinces.
</P>
<P>
The Thai interior ministry would prosecute every Laotian rebel
sneaking into Thailand, Sanoh said.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, the two sides reached a number of
agreements, including one on clearing obstacles to the border
demarcation which would start in the coming two weeks.
</P>
<P>
The governors of 11 Thai provinces and nine Laotian provinces
agreed to stop sand dredging along the Mekong river to avoid any
change in the course of the river which constitutes a natural
boundary between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The governors also agreed to ease travel restrictions across
the border to facilitate trade and tourism.  
</P>
</TEXT>
