<HEADLINE> Fengle Seed-Breeding Firm Listed at Shenzhen Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Hefei Fengle Seed-Breeding
Stocking Company Ltd. was listed at the Shenzhen Stock Exchange
today to become the first farm-related share on the bourse.
</P>
<P>
The newly-listed firm plans to sell 45 million shares through
the trading network of the Shenzhen exchange to gather 293 million
yuan. The funds will be used to upgrade its seed-breeding
production.
</P>
<P>
Local investors reponded favorably to the new issue today,
while local analysts predicted that more such issues will be
listed at the bourse in the future.
</P>
<P>
Fengle, which is located in Hefei, capital city of Anhui
Province in East China, is the country's largest watermelon
seed-breeding base. In 1996, it produced some 400,000 kg of
watermelon seeds.
</P>
<P>
The company also breeds seeds of other crops including paddy
rice, corn, cotton and vegetables, and produces pesticides and
other types of farm chemicals.
</P>
<P>
The company generated 33.13 million yuan in net profits in
1996.
</P>
<P>
Fengle has established business ties with over 100 companies in
a dozen foreign countries and regions.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
