<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Down Slightly on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices fell slightly on
the Singapore market amid fears of higher interest rates in the
United states, as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
lost 2.3 points to close at 2,075.78 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 163.26 million units,
valued at 353.78 million Singapore dollars (about 245.68 million
US dollars). Declines led advances by 202 to 114, while 288 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
New Toyo was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 7.16 million units. It was followed by MBF Holdings
which had 5.32 million shares traded. MBF Land was next with 4.43
million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local software maker Creative 50 topped the gainers' list of
the day as it surged by 3.3 Singapore dollars to finish at 16.9
Singapore dollars. Goodwood Park rose by one Singapore dollars to
end at 40 Singapore dollars, while the Development Bank of
Singapore (DBS) Foreign increased by 40 cents to close at 18.1
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Genting 200 was the biggest loser as it
declined by 65 cents to end at 8.95 dollars. The Thai Prime Fund
fell by 60 cents to close at 10.10 dollars, while the Singapore
Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign closed 50 cents lower at 27 Singapore
dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
