<HEADLINE> China-Made Washing Machine Meets Quality Standards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Statistics show that 92 percent of
domestically-made washing machines met state quality standards.
</P>
<P>
A sample survey of washing machines from 25 firms showed that
23 varieties are qualified, said today's "Market News."
</P>
<P>
Of the total surveyed, 100 percent of turbined, 66 percent of
cylinder, and 91 percent of double-tube models are up to standard.
</P>
<P>
Name-brand products are of higher quality, the survey said,
adding that some firms still need to raise their awareness of
quality.
</P>
<P>
China produced 11 million washing machines in a year. With the
improvement of living standards, 50 percent of rural families will
purchase washing machines in the coming few years, according to
the "Market News."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a large majority of the current 85 percent of urban
residents who own the machine need to "upgrade," since most of the
machines were purchased about ten years ago, said the newspaper.
</P>
</TEXT>
