<HEADLINE> APEC Deputy Finance Ministers Meet in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CEBU, The Philippines, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Deputy finance
ministers of 18 member economies of the Asia Pacific Economic
Cooperation (APEC) forum met here this afternoon to prepare for
the fourth APEC finance ministers' meeting.
</P>
<P>
The deputy finance ministers, joined by the deputy chiefs of
APEC members' central banks, discussed a joint statement to be
adopted by the finance ministers Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The joint statement contains measures proposed by the APEC
members to promote domestic financial and capital markets
development and facilitate private sector participation in
infrastructure development in the region.
</P>
<P>
The two-day APEC finance ministers' meeting, due to begin here
Saturday, will deliberate these measures and the ministers will
also have a dialogue with representatives from some private sector
groups in the Asia Pacific.
</P>
<P>
Also attending the finance ministers' meeting will be
representatives of the International Monetary Fund, the Asian
Development Bank, the APEC Business Advisory Council and the
Pacific Economic Council.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is a follow-up of the 4th APEC informal leadership
meeting held last November in Subic, the northern Philippines.
During that meeting, the leaders asked the finance ministers to
seek concrete and practical measures to accelerate the development
of financial and capital markets in the region.  
</P>
