<HEADLINE> Employment Pattern Changes in Jiangsu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The pattern in east China's
Jiangsu province has changed from state units to several sectors
now predominantly employing labor.
</P>
<P>
The non-state sectors employ more labor force in the province,
said the local government.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province reported a 2.2 percent of unemployment
rate, lower than the nation's average.
</P>
<P>
The employment structure has witnessed changes. Some 90 percent
of newly employed population are in the industrial and service
sectors.
</P>
<P>
People are now competing for their posts rather than relying on
distribution by the government as in previous years.
</P>
<P>
The local government has paid close attention to employment,
noting that low unemployment rate is of great importance to social
stability.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu, with its large population, is faced with heavy
employment pressure. To provide lay-offs with basic living
conditions, the local government last year granted relief funds of
154 million yuan, and provided new jobs for 243,000 or 50 percent
of the unemployed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
