<HEADLINE> Chinese Defense Minister Meets Swiss Army Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China attaches importance to its
relationship with the government and army of Switzerland, Chinese
Defense Minister Chi Haotian told Arthur Liener, Chief of the
General Staff of the Swiss armed forces, here today.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in the Great Hall of the People this
afternoon, Chi noted that the two countries share many common
points.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission and
a state councilor, told Liener that the Chinese people always
cherish deep friendly feelings toward the Swiss people.
</P>
<P>
He said that Liener's visit to China is trail-blazing and will
effectively promote understanding and trust between the two
countries and the two armies.
</P>
<P>
Liener is the first top-ranking Swiss military officer to visit
China.
</P>
<P>
Liener said that he has identified many common grounds between
the two armies during this visit, noting that both countries
pursue an independent foreign policy of peace and maintain a
defense policy totally for self-defense.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the wish that the two armies will strengthen their
links in a bid to promote contact, exchanges, understanding, and
friendship between the two countries and the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
He also conveyed Head of the Federal Military Department Adolf
Ogi's invitation for Chi to visit Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Chi, in reply, asked Liener to convey his invitation to Ogi to
visit China.
</P>
<P>
Liener arrived in China on Thursday. He will tour around the
country and return home on April 10.  
</P>
</TEXT>
