<HEADLINE> Thailand Backs China's Bid to Join WTO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Thai Commerce Minister has
confirmed Thailand's commitment to support China in its bid to
become a member of the World Trade Organization (WTO), according
to the Thai news agency (TNA) today.
</P>
<P>
Thai Commerce Minister Narongchai Akrasanee told the agency
that Thailand will give its full support to China's bid to become
a WTO member as it will help promote trade in the region, the TNA
quoted him as saying in Beijing on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The minister is accompanying Prime Minister Chavalit
Yongchaiyudh on a four-day official visit to China.
</P>
