<HEADLINE> Nigerian Women Won't Vote for Men </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian women have vowed not to
vote for any male candidates in subsequent elections if the
current negative attitude of male voters towards female
candidates does not change.
</P>
<P>
President of the National Council of Women Societies, Amina
Esther Sambo reportedly said in Katsina State on Wednesday that
Nigerian women have had enough of intrigues and discriminations
from men.
</P>
<P>
She complained of female candidates being threatened,
discriminated and frustrated out of contests by men in the March
15 local government elections, pointing out that this will do no
good to the country's transition to democracy program.
</P>
<P>
"If we must progress and attain the desired success in human
endeavor, male politicians must be prepared to accept their
female counterparts in every sphere," she said.
</P>
<P>
According to the president, of the over 700 local governments
in the country, women candidates only won in seven in the March
15 elections.
</P>
<P>
She said the council is determined to assist female candidates
with genuine complaints over the elections to take their cases to
the court. 
</P>
</TEXT>
