<HEADLINE> Mainland Universities to Recruit Macao Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Apart from the Ji'nan University and the Overseas Chinese
University, both mainly targeting overseas students, 96
universities and colleges across the mainland will admit Macao
students this year, an increase of more than 20 such institutions
from 1996.
</P>
<P>
Sources with the Macao Association of Chinese Education said
that Macao middle school students of under 25 years old, who will
graduate this year, can submit applications between April 10 to
17.
</P>
<P>
They can take the entrance examinations in late June after
their applications are accepted.
</P>
<P>
The number of Macao students entering mainland universities has
increased rapidly over the past decade. More than 1,000 students
applied last year and a total of 628 were admitted after
passing the entrance examinations.
</P>
<P>
And three years ago, some of the mainland universities started
to enroll outstanding Macao students free of entrance exams, a
move widely practiced in the mainland.
</P>
<P>
More than 90 outstanding Macao students were enrolled by 13
mainland universities this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
