<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Lusaka police have confiscated
thousands of suspected pirated video and audio tapes from shops
here, the Zambia Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
The surprise swoop was conducted shortly before shops closed
at 17 hours.
</P>
<P>
The police action followed numerous complaints by musicians
and others concerned on the notoriety of the affected shops.
</P>
<P>
A policeman on the spot said, ''we cannot tell you how many
tapes we have grabbed but they are from several shops. The
exercise was not only here.''
</P>
<P>
As policemen continued with their raid, word went round in the
city forcing street vendors dealting in video and audio tapes to
scamper in all directions.
</P>
<P>
The Zambian Union of Musicians (ZUM) recently complained of
the rising rate of piracy in the country. 
