<HEADLINE> Ericsson to Help East China Province Expand Mobile Networks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Ericsson company has
signed two contracts worth more than 80 million US dollars for the
expansion of the GSM and TACS mobile networks in east China's
Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
Jiangsu Province, one of China's major economic powerhouses,
will use Ericsson's switching and radio base equipment and
associated services, to carry out the expansion of the local GSM
(global system of mobile communications) network and the third
phase of TACS (total access cellular system).
</P>
<P>
The expansion is expected put into service by the end of the
year, to lift the handling capacity of the provincial GSM and TACS
networks to nearly one million and 300,000 subscribers,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Ericsson began supplying public switching equipment to the
coastal province in late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
China has become Ericsson's second largest market worldwide
after the US. Ericsson has set up 15 presentative offices and nine
joint ventures in China, providing a full range of
telecommunications solutions and services. 
</P>
