<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka To Launch Food Drive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government is to
launch a food drive in June this year and President Chandrika
Kumaratunga has promised all necessary incentives to get the
private sector involved in the project, officials said today.
</P>
<P>
Kumaratunga stressed the urgency of the drive yesterday at a
meeting which discussed the government's New Agricultural Policy.
</P>
<P>
She promised all necessary incentives such as credit, tariff
and other methods to involve the private sector in the project,
the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Farmer organizations and farmer companies with management and
service skills will be set up to handle procurement and the
marketing of products.
</P>
<P>
Concessionary credit facilities will be offered to the
agricultural sector to generate self employment. Interest rates
will be as low as 10 percent and about 500,000 youths are expected
to benefit from it.
</P>
<P>
A working group has been requested to take necessary steps to
implement the proposals and strategies in the action plan for the
food drive.  
