<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Scores Over $2 Billion Trade Surplus in January </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, April 4 (Xinhua) -- France scored a 11.723 billion
francs (about 2.13 billion U.S. dollar) trade surplus in January,
against 8.528 billion francs (about 1.55 billion dollars) in
December 1996, said the French Customs today.
</P>
<P>
In January, France exported 125.112 billion francs (about 22.7
billion dollars) worth of goods and imported 113.389 billion
francs (about 20.57 billion dollars) of goods.
</P>
<P>
Its export of agriculture and food products registered a 4.512
billion francs (about 820 million dollars) of surplus, while
energy products registered a deficit of 8.855 billion francs
(about 1.61 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
The surplus in export of military materials increased from
7.989 billion francs (about 1.45 billion dollars) in December to
11.156 billion francs (about 2.03 billion dollars) in January.
</P>
<P>
Eight Airbus passenger carriers were sold in the month at a
value of 3.109 billion francs (about 560 million dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
