<HEADLINE> Serbia Opposes Internationalization of Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The ruling Socialist Party of
Serbia (SPS) today denounced a U.S. political organ for its
intention to internationalize the Kosovo issue of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Ivica Dacic, spokesman for the SPS, said that his party will
not send representatives to the New York roundtable talks --
"Kosovo Serbian-Albanian Ethnics Dialogue" -- sponsored by the
U.S. organization known as "Project on National Relations."
</P>
<P>
"Kosovo is an inalienable part of Serbia, and the ethnic
problem there is Serbia's internal affair," Dacic said.
</P>
<P>
"Any attempt to internationalize the Kosovo issue is
unnecessary and harmful, and the issue could only be settled on
the basis of respects of Serbia's independence, sovereignty and
territorial integrity," he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the SPS executive committee in Kosovo Province also
declared on Thursday that "no one can take advantage of the Kosovo
issue" and its internationalization could only "lead to civil war
in Serbia."
</P>
<P>
Serbia has been troubled by the demand of the ethnic Albanians
in Kosovo for independence since the beginning of 1980s. 
</P>
</TEXT>
