<HEADLINE> Foreign Funds Help to Boost North Province's Forestry Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, April 4 (Xinhua) -- With the aid of foreign funds the
forestry sector in north China's Shanxi province has reaped
significant economic and ecological gains.
</P>
<P>
To date, 23.76 million US dollars of foreign donations and
loans from Germany, Italy and other countries have been used in
the province's afforestation efforts and forest products
production.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-German forestry technological cooperation project,
which was started 12 years ago, has contributed greatly to the
establishment of China's biggest gene base for poplar, which
collects approximately 1,000 poplar strains from both China and
overseas.
</P>
<P>
As a result of the forestry technological cooperation between
China and Germany, 35 selected poplar strains have been spread to
12 provinces or autonomous regions in China, and their techniques
also increased the survival rate of poplars by 10 to 20 percent
and cut the planting cost by some 20 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
