<DOCNO> XIE19970404.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: ABCs of Basic Law of Hong Kong SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Today is the seventh anniversary
of the promulgation of the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
It is an accurate and complete embodiment of the great concept
of "one country, two systems" in the form of a national law. As a
legal code, it is of fundamental importance in maintaining the
prosperity and stability of Hong Kong after it returns to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
In order to help readers become better acquainted with the
Basic Law, the Xinhua News Agency will publish the ABCs of the
Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region both in
Chinese and English in a question-and-answer format beginning
today.
</P>
<P>
The following are the ABCs of the Basic Law (1-2):
</P>
<P>
Question: Why was a Basic Law for the Hong Kong SAR enacted?
When does its implementation begin?
</P>
<P>
Answer: The Sino-British Joint Declaration, apart from
specifying the Chinese government's basic policies regarding Hong
Kong, contains this provision: "The above-stated basic policies of
the People's Republic of China regarding Hong Kong and the
elaboration of them in Annex 1 to this Joint Declaration will be
stipulated, in a Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region of the People's Republic of China, by the National People's
Congress of the People's Republic of China, and they will remain
unchanged for 50 years." Annex 1 to the Joint Declaration has a
similar provision.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government systematically states its basic policies
regarding Hong Kong in the Joint Declaration. It is far from
sufficient, however, to have these policies represented in
diplomatic documents only. They must be enshrined in a state law
so as to be legally binding over a long period of time. In
addition, enactment of a Basic Law for the Hong Kong SAR is a
commitment made by the Chinese government in the Joint
Declaration. On the day when the Sino-British Joint Declaration
took effect, Hong Kong entered its transitional period. The
drafting and enactment of a Basic Law for the Hong Kong SAR became
a work of the greatest importance within this transitional period.
</P>
<P>
On April 4, 1990, the Third Session of the Seventh National
People's Congress adopted the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China, and
decided that the Basic Law shall take effect as of July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Question: How did the Basic Law come into being?
</P>
<P>
Answer: On April 10, 1985, the Sixth National People's Congress
decided to establish a Drafting Committee for the Basic Law of the
Hong Kong SAR. On June 18 of the same year, the NPC Standing
Committee adopted a list of members for the committee. The
committee was composed of 59 personages from various social
circles and specialists, including 23 Hong Kongers. (By the ninth
meeting of the committee, membership had decreased to 51,
including 18 from Hong Kong, as four had died, two resigned, and
two been removed for conduct that was incompatible with their
capacity).
</P>
<P>
On July 1, 1985, the Drafting Committee was officially
established and began its work. During the four years and eight
months after its formation, the committee held nine plenary
sessions and 73 group meetings dealing with special issues. In the
meantime, a Basic Law Consultation Committee, composed of 180
representatives from social circles in Hong Kong, was established
to act as a bridge of communication between Hong Kong residents
and the Drafting Committee and a channel for Hong Kong people to
express their opinions and suggestions.
</P>
<P>
In 1988, a draft of the Basic Law of the Hong Kong SAR was
completed and circulated to solicit views extensively in Hong Kong
and the inland areas for revision. At the end of 1988 and in early
1989, after examination by the NPC Standing Committee, the Hong
Kong Basic Law (Draft) was made public in an effort to solicit
more opinions and make further revisions. The final draft of the
law was submitted to the NPC in April 1990 and was adopted and
officially promulgated.
</P>
<P>
The Basic Law is an embodiment of the collective wisdom,
creativity and hard work of many people in Hong Kong and the
inland areas. Its drafting process is one of full and extensive
democratic consultations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970404.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Contest for Young Fashion Designers in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Young fashion designers from five
continents are to vie for glamor in the fifth Brother Cup China
International Young Fashion Designers Contest, which is due to be
held in April 11 in the Chinese capital.
</P>
