<HEADLINE> Greening Drive Begins in Southwest Chinese Cities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- A large-scale drive to green up
major cities of southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region
such as Nanning, the regional capital, and Guilin, the popular
tourist attraction, has begun.
</P>
<P>
March has become the "green month" (tree planting) in Nanning.
Last month, a large number of volunteers in the city participated
tree planting activities.
</P>
<P>
"Our target is to win the national `garden-like city' award,"
said one local official.
</P>
<P>
In Guilin, best known its picturesque rivers and mountains, the
government's goal this year was to plant 150,000 trees and
increasing the forest and green coverage in urban areas to 33.8
and 31 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
According to a municipal government official in Guilin, by the
end of this year the per capita green space in the city will be
5.5 sq m.
</P>
<P>
In Yulin, the city government has decided to spend 30 million
yuan (some 3.7 million US dollars) on an urban greening program.
</P>
</TEXT>
