<HEADLINE> 700 More Zairean Refugees Arrive in Zambia's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 700 Zairean refugees
have arrived in Zambia's Luapula Province, according to a report
received here today.
</P>
<P>
The refugees are fleeing the continued armed conflicts in
eastern Zaire.
</P>
<P>
However, the report quoted Luapula Province Minister Norman
Chibamba as saying yesterday in the provincial capital Mansa that
out of the 200 refugees who had been kept in a refugee camp in
the province earlier, 100 had returned to Zaire.
</P>
<P>
Chibamba said that although refugees kept criss-crossing the
border, the situation was under control.
</P>
<P>
However, he said that there was need for more logistics to
help officers monitoring the situation. "We need more vehicles
and boats for those patrolling the Luapula River but we are doing
our best with the limited resources," the province minister said.
</P>
<P>
The Luapula River is a border river between Zambia and Zaire.
</P>
