<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets Vietnamese Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin said
that in a complex and ever-changing world, furthering traditional
Sino-Vietnamese friendship and cooperation is not only in the
fundamental interest of the two peoples, but contributes to peace
and stability in Southeast Asia and the whole Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general-secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), met this morning with Le Minh
Huong, member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of
the Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV) and minister of the Interior,
and his party.
</P>
<P>
