<HEADLINE> 41 People Killed In Flood In Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 4 (Xinhua) -- 41 people has died in Lindi
region, southeastern Tanzania in flood caused by heavy rains,
Daily News reported today.
</P>
<P>
Regional Administrative Secretary (RAS) Charles Ponella was
quoted as saying that 15 bodies were recovered at Mandawa village
while 2 were found at Mchinga village in Lindi Rural District.
</P>
<P>
He said that 11 other people from Mandawa village are still
missing and feared to have died in the floods.
</P>
<P>
Mandawa villagers early on Wednesday morning recovered 20
bodies and two bodies were fished out on Tuesday. 20 more people
were reportedly missing.
</P>
<P>
All the recovered bodies have been buried, he further said.
</P>
<P>
According to reports, Linid Regional Commissioner (RC),
Abubakar Mgumia with his defense and security committee left for
Mandawa village to make on-the-spot assessment of the disaster.
</P>
<P>
The RC also said that 353 passengers who were travelling from
Dar es Salaam to Lindi and Mtwara and from the southern regions
to Dar es Salaam are still stranded at Nangurukuru and Matandu in
Kilwa District.
</P>
<P>
The floods have also rendered homeless more than 2,000 at
Kilwa Kivinje, where 64 houses were washed away.
</P>
<P>
However, the Ministry of Home Affairs had provided a
helicopter to be stationed at Samanga on the border between Kilwa
and Rufiji districts to provide transport to the affected areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
