<DOCNO> XIE19970404.0189 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> PLA Garrison To Be Stationed in HK to Strictly Abide by Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA) garrison in Hong Kong shall act as ordinary members of
the Hong Kong society and abide by the Hong Kong laws and the
military disciplines, said Major General Xiong Ziren, political
commissar of the PLA Garrison to be stationed in Hong Kong after
June 30.
</P>
<P>
At a seminar held here today to mark the 7th Anniversary of the
 promulgation of the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), Xiong said that should any of PLA
members violate the law or commit crimes, they will be handled
strictly according to the Garrison Law.
</P>
<P>
He said that those who violate the law when they are not on
duties will be handled according to the SAR laws through the SAR
judiciary.
</P>
<P>
He said that members of the garrison shall not join any of the
political, religious, or social organizations or associations of
the HKSAR, and they shall not engage in profit-making activities
or take part in any activities incompatible with their status as
members of the military.
</P>
<P>
He said that the PLA garrison in Hong Kong will certainly
strive to live up to the expectations of the country and the
Chinese people and act to the satisfaction of the Hong Kong
compatriots.
</P>
<P>
He said that since the Basic Law is not only the constitution
of the HKSAR but also the law of China, the people of the Chinese
inland areas shall also abide by it.
</P>
<P>
He said that the PLA garrison in Hong Kong will be mainly
responsible for the defense of the HKSAR.
</P>
<P>
He outlined the duties of the garrison as follows: to prevent
and resist invasion and protect the security of the HKSAR; to
assume defense duties; to manage the military facilities and to
handle as appropriate matters pertaining to external military
affairs.
</P>
<P>
He said that the PLA garrison in Hong Kong will respect the
political structure, social system and life style of the HKSAR,
and treasure the public properties, private properties of the
residents and other people of the HKSAR. 
</P>
</TEXT>
