<HEADLINE> Zambian Maize Yield Expected to Reach Over One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian Ministry of
Agriculture, Food and Fisheries has predicted that the country's
maize production of the current harvest season may reach
1,377,000 tons over the last season's 1,080,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
The latest prediction available from the ministry is based on
figures collected in January and February. It cleared the
pessimistic prediction made at the beginning of the season that
the maize output might drop.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of the current harvest season, the weather
conditions were not so good. However, they have changed for the
better later with enough rain.
</P>
<P>
Zambia National Farmers Union Executive Director George Gray
said he agrees with the ministry's preliminary crop forecast. But
he indicated that since January the crop has faced an adverse
weather and some diseases, which might result in some damage.
</P>
<P>
There are persistent rains in recent weeks and more diseases
are found in the fields. They may bring damages to some crops
still in the field and reduce the output. 
</P>
</TEXT>
