<HEADLINE> Sino-Pakistani Joint Expedition to Climb Mt. Qomolangma </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Pakistani joint expedition,
headed by Pakistan's Nazir Ahmed Sabir, will attempt to conquer
the Mt. Qomolangma on April 10.
</P>
<P>
The joint expedition, which aims to celebrate the China's
recovery over Hong Kong and mark the 50th anniversary of the
independence of Pakistan, has 15 climbers including five Chinese
and 10 Pakistanis.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time for the two countries to join hands in
mountaineering. No Pakistanis have scaled the world's highest
peak in history.
</P>
<P>
In late April, the two countries will also send another joint
expedition to overcome the world's ninth-highest peak Mt. Nanga
Parbat, which stands 8,125 meters and lies in Pakistan. 
</P>
