<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Zhou Guangzhou, president of the
Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), has urged Chinese researchers to
have a patriotic motive in working for the country.
</P>
<P>
Zhou was present at a flag-raising ceremony this morning in
front of CAS's Beijing headquarters. Also present were CAS
vice-presidents Yan Yixun, Xu Zhihong, and Chen Yiyu, nearly 500
staff members, and academicians including the mathematician Yang
Le, electrical engineering expert Yan Luguang, and mineralogist
Xie Xiande.
</P>
<P>
This was CAS's first flag-raising ceremony at its headquarters,
and an important decision of its top leaders to promote socialist
cultural and ethical progress, Zhou explained in brief remarks.
</P>
<P>
"It is designed to further arouse scientific researchers'
patriotism," he said, highlighting staff members' immense devotion
to the country's construction over the past four decades.
</P>
<P>
He said that today's science and technology researchers bear
much more responsibility in making contributions to the country's
prosperity.
</P>
<P>
He encouraged them to carry forward the fine tradition of
scientists of the older generation to love and serve the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
CAS has made a rule that a flag-raising ceremony will be held
on the first working day of each month from now on. At least one
CAS leader will raise the national flag on that day. 
