<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Fruitful in Scientific, Technological fields in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China was fruitful in the fields
of scientific and technological research in 1996, according to an
annual report by the State Statistics Bureau published today.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the country had a total of 27.59
million professionals and technicians of all specialization
working working in state-owned enterprises and institutions, up
two percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
There were 23,304 research institutions of various kinds, with
a total staff of 2.8 million including 1.59 million scientists and
engineers.
</P>
<P>
A total of 89.9 billion billion yuan were invested in
scientific and technological activities last year, up 8.6 percent
year-on-year. Of the total, 32.7 billion yuan was spent on
research and development (R&AMP;D), accounting for 0.5 percent of the
gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the country achieved 31,000 key results in scientific
researches, 647 of which received prizes from the state.
</P>
<P>
Last year, a total of 103,00 applications for patent were
received from domestic and overseas applicants, while 44,000
patents were authorized.
</P>
<P>
New progress was made in the cooperation between enterprises
and higher education and research institutions in 1996, and some
675,000 people from 45,000 enterprises and education institutions
participated in 15,800 cooperative projects of this nature.
</P>
<P>
In the year, the country also set up 88 state engineering or
technological research centers, five state industrial bases and 40
state-level enterprise technical centers.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the country established 1,441 urban
and rural weather warning and service stations and 190 satellite
cloud map receiving stations, and meanwhile, 81,396 maps of
various scales were prepared by mapping departments and 983 kinds
of maps were published.
</P>
<P>
Markets for the transfer of technology became more brisk last
year, with a total of 226,000 contracts on the transfer of
technology were signed, involving a transaction value of 30
billion yuan, up by 2.1 percent and 11.8 percent respectively over
the previous year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
