<HEADLINE> China Controls Population Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China made new headway in its
family planning programme in 1996, according to a communique
released by the State Statistics Bureau here today.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that in 1996, the crude birth rate of
population in China was 16.98 per thousand, and the crude death
rate was 6.56 per thousand, resulting in a natural growth rate of
10.42 per thousand.
</P>
<P>
At the end of 1996, the total population of China was 1,223.89
million, an increase of 12.68 million over the figure at the end
of 1995.
</P>
<P>
The average size of household was 3.70 persons in 1996. The
proportion of population aged 0-14 was 26.4 percent, those aged
15-64 was 67.2 percent and that of people aged 65 and over was 6.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
The average life expectancy of the population was 70.80 years,
that for male was 68.71 and for female, 73.04, said the
statistics.  
</P>
</TEXT>
