<HEADLINE> China Enhances Environment Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China's environmental protection
was further enhanced in 1996, according to a report released here
today by the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that at the end of 1996, there were 92,000
people working in national environmental protection system that
included, among others, 2,157 monitoring stations. China had 799
natural reserves, covering a total area of 71.85 million ha and
accounting for 7.19 percent of the total area of the country.
</P>
<P>
The legal construction for protecting the environment
accelerated last year, says the report, adding that 374 standards
concerning environmental protection were formulated.
</P>
<P>
Among all construction projects started in 1996, 86.7 percent
of them implemented the evaluation program on the impact of the
projects in question on the environment.
</P>
<P>
In addition, 57,430 heavy-pollution producing enterprises were
banned, closed or suspended, accounting for 81.2 percent of all 15
categories of heavy-pollution producing enterprises that should
have been dealt with. 
</P>
</TEXT>
