<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australia on Course to Davis Cup Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Australia gained a 2-0 lead over
Czech Republic after the first two singles in their Davis Cup
quarter final in Adelaide, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Patrick Rafter got Australia off to a great start by beating
the top Czech player Martin Damm 6-1, 7-6 (9-7), 4-6, 6-4 in 152
minutes in the first singles.
</P>
<P>
Australian number one Mark Philippoussis completed Australia's
clean sweep of the opening singles when he powered past David Cup
new hand David Rikl 6-4, 2-6, 6-4 in 115 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Australia was believed to have ensured the win since top world
doubles pair Mark Woodforde and Todd Woodbridge will play the
doubles on Saturday against Rikl and Pavel Vizner.
</P>
<P>
Rikl, a lefthander ranked 183, was a last-minute replacement
for Jiri Novak who was ruled out with flu overnight.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Philippoussis made full use of his powerful
service, notching up more than a dozen aces.  
</P>
</TEXT>
