<HEADLINE> China's Energy production Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China's total energy production
(standard fuel equivalent) amounted to 1.26 billion tons in 1996,
a rise of 4.6 percent over 1995, according to the State Statistics
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The country produced 1.38 billion tons of coal in 1996, an
increase of 4.5 percent, and pumped out 158 million tons of crude
oil, a rise of 5.3 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country also generated 1,075 billion kw/hours of
electricity in 1996, a rise of 6.7 percent over 1995. 
</P>
