<HEADLINE> China's Steel Production Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China produced 101.1 million tons
of steel in 1996, a rise of six percent over 1995, according
to the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
A communique released by the bureau showed that the country
also produced 86.11 million tons of rolled steel in 1996, up 6.1
percent over 1995 and turned out 4.7 million tons of ten kinds of
nonferrous metals, up five percent.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, China turned out 490 million tons of cement, a rise of
3.2 percent; and 67.32 million cu m of timber, a fall of 0.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
The country produced 18.89 million tons of sulfuric acid in
1996, a rise of 4.3 percent over 1995; 6.64 million tons of soda
ash, a rise of 11.2 percent and 3.01 million tons of ethylene, a
rise of 25.4 percent. 
