<HEADLINE> China Builds More Motor Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China built 1.49 million motor
vehicles in 1996, a rise of 2.6 percent over 1995, according to
the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
A communique released by the bureau today shows that of the
total, 390,000 were cars, a rise of 15.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The country also produced 26.6 million tons of chemical
fertilizers, an increase of 4.4 percent; and 430,000
tons of chemical insecticides, a rise of 3.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
