<HEADLINE> China Finishes Construction of 134 Large, Medium-Sized Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China completed 134 large and
medium-sized projects in 1996, including 33 state key projects,
according to sources from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The newly-increased production capacity through capital
construction projects included: 10.45 million tons of coal mining,
15.25 million kw of power generation, 19.73 million tons of oil
extraction and 4.4 billion cu m of natural gas, 2.5 million tons
of iron, 290,000 vehicles, 740,000 tons of ethylene, 1.51 million
tons of chemical fertilizers, 290,000 cu m of timber felling.
</P>
<P>
Last year also saw the completion of 1,954 km of new railway
lines, 1,522 km of double-track railways, 3.4 million tons of
cargo handling capacity of harbors, 21.07 million lines of
handling capacity of urban telephone switchboards, 20,000 km of
long-distance fiber-optical cable, 10,000 km of microwave digital
telecommunication lines, and 1,117 km of expressways.
</P>
<P>
A total of 81,974 capital construction and technical updating
projects were completed and put into operation in 1996, accounting
for 54.2 percent of all projects that were under construction
during the year.
</P>
<P>
The newly increased fixed assets reached 723.8 billion yuan,
the rate of fixed assets put into use was 59.6 percent, or 0.4
percentage points higher.
</P>
<P>
The completed floor space of housing was 235.23 million sq m,
44.9 percent of the total floor space under construction, or 0.2
percentage points higher than that in the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
