<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment in China Sees Steady Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China actually utilized 55.27
billion US dollars last year, up 14.2 percent than the previous
year, according a report from China's State Statistics Bureau
(SSB) released here today.
</P>
<P>
According to a SSB official, foreign capital steadily flew into
China last year. Foreign capital actually used by the country last
year totalled 55.27 billion dollars, up 14.2 percent over the
previous year. Of the total, 42.35 billion dollars was in the form
of direct foreign investment, up 12.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The structure of foreign investment was also further
improved. More foreign investment was poured in fields of
infrastructure, basic industries, pillar industries, and in those
capital- or technology-intensive projects. 
</P>
