<HEADLINE> Rafter Beats Damm to Give Australia 1-0 Lead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Pat Rafter gave Australia a 1-0
lead over the Czech Republic by beating Martin Damm in the opener
of their Davis Cup quarter-final tie in Adelaide on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Rafter won over the 44th-ranked Damm 6-1, 7-6 (9-7), 4-6, 6-4
in a tussle lasting two hours and 41 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, ranked 43 in the world, took advantage of his greater
experience on grass to dominate against Damm.
</P>
<P>
The Czechs, who were playing without four top players, suffered
another blow earlier on Friday when Jiri Novak was forced to pull
out of the second singles rubber against Mark Philippoussis
because of a virus.
</P>
<P>
Novak, ranked 60, complained of a high temperature and was
ruled out after a medical examination.
</P>
<P>
Australia upset holders France 4-1 in Sydney in the previous
round, while the Czechs defeated India 3-2. The winner of the tie
will take on either the United States or the Netherlands. 
</P>
</TEXT>
