<HEADLINE> China Investing 2,366 Billion Yuan on Fixed Assets in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China invested 2,366 billion yuan
in fixed assets in 1996, a rise of 18.2 percent over the previous
year, according to sources from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Of this total, the investment completed in agriculture,
forestry, animal husbandry, fishery and water conservancy was 33.6
billion yuan, up 27.5 percent, and its share in the total
investment rose from 1.8 percent to 1.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The energy sector completed 293.8 billion yuan in fixed assets,
up 21.1 percent over the previous year, its proportion rose from
16.7 percent to 16.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Investment in raw materials was 150.5 billion yuan, up 2.9
percent; that in machine-building and electronics industries was
87.2 billion yuan, up 21.1 percent; that in light and textile
industries was 99.9 billion yuan, up 10.7 percent; that in
transportation and telecommunications was 301.2 billion yuan, up
22.1 percent. 
