<HEADLINE> Malaria Deaths Shoot up in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's national malaria death
toll has shot up to 419, while 223,594 cases have been reported
since the beginning of the year, a spokesman for the health
ministry said in Harare yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics, which was reflective of the week ending
March 23, shows that 56 people died in one week countrywide,
while up to 25,893 malaria cases were reported during that
period.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said, "the national trend shows an increase of
three percent in the number of cases reported during the week
ending March 23." 
