<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hke - Referendum Date Set for Poland's New Constitution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Poland will go to the polls on May
25 to vote on the country's new constitution to replace the
old one created 45 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Polish President Alexander Kwasniewski announced the date last
night after the National Assembly passed the new draft on its
final reading with two thirds of legislators voting for it.
</P>
<P>
The new constitution, which deputies in the Assembly began to
draw up in 1993, will be implemented after referendum.
</P>
<P>
The constitution, the 11th in Polish history, contains 243
articles in 13 chapters, and sets out a number of economic,
political and social guarantees.
</P>
<P>
It enshrines Poland's economic system as a social market
economy, based on the freedom of economic enterprise and private
property. It also guarantees minimum levels of social security
for the population.
</P>
<P>
Parliament will be allowed to overturn the president's veto
with three-fifths of the votes in the lower house rather than the
present two-thirds majority.
</P>
<P>
The draft enshrines equal rights for all churches and religious
organizations and the state's impartiality towards different
religious beliefs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
