<HEADLINE> China Spending 2,366 Billion Yuan on Fixed Assets in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China invested 2,366 billion yuan
in fixed assets in 1996, a rise of 18.2 percent over the previous
year, according to sources from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Of this total, the investment of state-owned units was 1,235.9
billion yuan, up 13.4 percent; of the collective units, 349
billion yuan, an increase of 6.1 percent; of urban and rural
residents, 333 billion yuan, up 30.1 percent; and of other types
of ownership, 448.1 billion yuan, up 37 percent.
