<HEADLINE> China Fruitful in Culture, Health-Care, Sports in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China made remarkable achievements
in the fields of culture, health-care and physical culture in 1996,
according to an annual report of the State Statistics Bureau
published today.
</P>
<P>
At the end of 1996, China had 2,685 art-performing groups,
2,864 culture centers, 2,641 public libraries, 1,205 museums,
3,600 archieves, 1,238 radio broadcasting stations, 880 television
stations, and 69,000 film-projection units.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, China produced 110 feature films and distributed 174
new movies, and eleven Chinese movies were awarded 14
international prizes.
</P>
<P>
A total of 18.1 billion copies of national and provincial
newspapers were issued last year, while 2.44 billion copies of
magazines and 7.08 copies of books were published.
</P>
<P>
At the end of last year, the country had 189,000 health-care
institutions with a total of 3.1 million beds, including 2.87
million beds in hospitals and health stations, up 1.1 percent over
the the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The number of health workers reached 4,310,000 including
1,380,000 doctors, up six percent over the previous year, and
1,020,000 nurses, up 3.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
At the end of 1996, the country had 5,887 sanitations and
anti-epidemic stations, with a total staff of 214,000, up 0.9
percent year-on-year; 3,254 maternal and child health-care
institutions, with a total staff of 140,000, up 4.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
The countryside had 51,277 medical institutions, with 735,000
beds, up 0.2 percent year-on-year, and a total staff of 940,000,
up 2.5 percent. Some 89.1 percent of rural villages had
medical-care stations, with a total staff of 1,320,000.
</P>
<P>
The year 1996 also witnessed significant progress in the
sports sector, according to the report.
</P>
<P>
Chinese athletes won 16 gold medals, 22 silver medals and 12
bronze medals in the Atlantic Olympic Games, making China the
fourth in the medal tally.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Chinese won 75 world champions in 17 events in the
national and international sporting games.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, mass sports activities were brisk last year as about
89 percent of students in schools met the requirements of the
National Standards for Physical Exercises. 
</P>
</TEXT>
