<HEADLINE> Child Kidnapping Causes Terror in Nepali Border Town </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Nepal's southern border town
Birgunj is on the edge of a public panic after a series of child
kidnapping cases occurred since last month, the local press here
said today.
</P>
<P>
The criminal wave has caused terror among local wealthy parents
who these days fear that their children might be kidnapped for
ransom on their way home from school, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The latest victim was a 12-year-old boy who disappeared on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Police have started a search operation in the area around the
town on Nepal-India border, about 80 km south of Kathmandu, but
so far the son of a local businessman has not yet been traced.
</P>
<P>
Two similar kidnapping cases took place last month in the area
with one kidnapped boy finally being tracked down by local police
with the help from Indian police in a nearby Indian town, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
Local businessmen of the Nepali border town have urged the
government to take strict measures against the crime of child
abduction and threatened to shut down the market if police fail to
arrest the criminals.
</P>
<P>
A local police officer said that the crime of child kidnapping
was on the rise mainly due to the absence of strong anti-abduction
laws in the country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
