<HEADLINE> Fire Destroys 100 Houses in Jakarta, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- A fire destroyed at least 100
houses in the crowded Kartini subdistrict in central Jakarta
Thursday, leaving hundreds of people homeless, official sources
here said today.
</P>
<P>
Two persons suffered minor burns and one was treated at the
Husada hospital, west Jakarta, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The fire razed through from 11:00 a.m. to 17:00 p.m., gutted
houses on two streets. Losses are estimated at hundreds of
billions of rupiah (one US dollar equals 2,340 rupiah). Asri
Ilyas, the head of the district said.
</P>
<P>
An electrical short circuit in a house is believed to be the
cause, central Jakarta fire fighters chief Freddy Aling said.
</P>
<P>
At least seven people have been killed and thousands left
homeless in more than 40 fires in the capital city in the last
four months, according to official statistics. 
</P>
