<HEADLINE> China Maintains Steady Growth in Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China scored steady growth in
industrial production in 1996, with industrial added value
totaling 2,858 billion yuan, up 12.7 percent from 1995,
according to the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Of the total growth, that of state-owned enterprises was 6.4
percent; that of collective enterprises was 17.4 percent; that of
foreign-backed enterprises was 13.1 percent; that of large and
medium-sized enterprises was 7.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
Light and heavy industries kept the same growth pace in 1996,
with the added value of the light industry reaching 1,193.8
billion yuan, up by 13.1 percent over the previous year; and that
of the heavy industry amounting to 1,664.2 billion yuan, up 12.4
percent.
</P>
<P>
Because of changes in market demand, there were increases and
decreases in production of major industrial products in
1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
