<HEADLINE> 300 Tamil Rebel Suspects Arrested In Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 4 (Xinhua) -- A combined Sri Lankan security
forces operation in several areas of Colombo Thursday resulted in
the arrest of 300 LTTE (Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam)
suspects, according to police sources here today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that these suspects are reported to have
infiltrated into Colombo in recent weeks from the North and East
with the specific purpose of creating chaos and to assassinate
VIPs in the city.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of security men were engaged in the cordon and
search operation which was conducted for over five hours to flush
out the rebels who are reported to have been staying in safe
houses and lodgings, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
They noted that the LTTE which has been fighting for a separate
state, has suffered several reversals in recent months at the
hands of the security forces in the North and East of the country,
and it is now adopting tactics of attacking civilian targets in
crowded areas.
</P>
<P>
Security has been strengthened in the whole city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
