<HEADLINE> China's Grain Output Set A New Record in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China's grain output hit 490
million tons in 1996, an all time high, said Zhang Sai, director
of State Statistics Bureau at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
The total grain output of 1996 represented an increase of five
percent over the previous year, and the country's agricultural
sector enjoyed a sharp increase last year, he added.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhang, the outputs of oil-bearing crops and cotton
went down slightly, standing at 22 million tons and 4.2 million
tons respectively.
</P>
<P>
In the mean time, the new afforested areas were 4.709 million
hectares, and the structure of the forestry industry had been
adjusted.
</P>
<P>
The output of meat last year hit 58 million tons, up 10.3
percent over the previous year; and the aquatic products
registered 28 million tons, an increase of 11.2 percent over the
1995 figure, Zhang said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
