<HEADLINE> China's Market Price Growth Slows down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China made a significant
achievement in curbing inflation in 1996, with the increase rate
of market prices slowing down continuously, Zhang Sai, director of
the State Statistics Bureau, announced at a press conference here
today.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the retail price index and consumer price index were
up 6.1 percent and 8.3 percent, respectively, over the previous
year. The growth rate was down by 8.7 and 8.8 percentage points
respectively, within the range of the price control target.
</P>
<P>
However, prices of some products, especially those of service
items, were still high. 
</P>
