<HEADLINE> CCB to Issue Floating Bonds in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank (CCB)
will issue 200 million US dollars of floating bond in Hong Kong
today.
</P>
<P>
The bonds will be listed in the Hong Kong United Stock Exchange
on April 14, said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The bank, a long-time lending institution for the country's
capital construction projects, would invest funds from the issue
in eight large domestic projects, including a 300,000-ton ethylene
project in Maoming, Guangdong Province, and the Shanghai Yangcheng
Power Station, a bank official was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The bank also intended to reinforce its ties with investors in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The issue enjoys a favorable climate because the price of
Chinese bonds has been growing since last year as the country's
economic conditions improved, the official said, adding that Asian
investors are very interested in Chinese bonds.
</P>
<P>
The floating rate notes issued this time have a five-year
maturity and carry a coupon of 30 basic points over the London
Interbank Offered Rate, a gauge for international interest rates.
</P>
<P>
CCB began to take part in the international capital market in
1988. By the end of last year, it has raised more than seven
billion US dollars in external funds, including more than 600
million US dollars of bonds.  
</P>
</TEXT>
