<HEADLINE> Thai Auto Exports Soar 85 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's exports of vehicles and
parts hit 3.22 billion baht (128.8 million US dollars) in the
first two months of this year, up 84.7 percent over the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Thailand exported 4,241 assembled autos worth 55.1 million US
dollars in January and February this year, up 391.43 percent in
volume and 544.97 percent in value, according to the Federation of
Thai Industries' Automobile Industry Club.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the country's exports of engines posted
234.79 million baht (9.4 million dollars) in value, up 60.1
percent, while components and spare parts exported valued 388.4
million baht (15.5 million dollars), up 295.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 25,955 motorcycles worth 881.75 million baht (35.3
million dollars) were shipped out of Thailand in the first two
months of this year, up 32.8 percent in volume and 28.7 percent in
value.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Thailand's exports of motorcycle components were
worth 294.8 million baht (11.8 million dollars) during the period,
up 590.5 percent, while its exports of motorcycle parts totaled
46.95 million baht in value, a rise of 552.1 percent. 
</P>
