<DOCNO> XIE19970404.0264 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Domestic Market Ample and Brisk in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China's domestic market of
consumer goods was ample and brisk last year. Meanwhile, the
country reached the targets set for the price control, according
to a report from China's State Statistics Bureau (SSB) released
here today.
</P>
<P>
The total retail sales of consumer goods was 2,461.4 billion
yuan, an increase of 19.4 percent over the previous year, with a
real growth of 12.5 percent if price hike was deducted.
</P>
<P>
In terms of urban and rural areas, the total retail sales of
consumer goods in urban areas reached 1,492.1 billion yuan, up
20.1 percent over that in the previous year. The total retail
sales of consumer goods at and below county level was 969.3
billion yuan, a rise of 18.3 percent. If the price increase was
deducted, the real growth was 13.5 percent and 11.2 percent,
respectively, in urban and rural areas.
</P>
<P>
In terms of different ownership, the retail sales of
state-owned outlets was 678.7 billion yuan, up nine percent; that
of collective outlets was 468.7 billion yuan, a rise of 13.5
percent; private outlets, 79.1 billion yuan, an increase of 40.6
percent; and outlets of other forms of ownership, 1,235.1 billion
yuan, up 27.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
According to a SSB official, significant achievement was
achieved in curbing inflation. The increase rate of market prices
went downward continuously. The retail price index and consumer
price index went up 6.1 percent and 8.3 percent, respectively,
over the previous year. Compared with the previous year, the
growth rate was down 8.7 and 8.8 percent respectively, within the
range of price control.
</P>
<P>
However, the prices of some products, especially prices for
service items remained high.  
</P>
</TEXT>
