<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Association of South
East Asian Nations (ASEAN) and the Southern Common Market
(Mercosur) are to set up an entrepreneurial council to boost trade
between the two blocs.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the council will be formalized during the
28th Meeting of ASEAN Economy Ministers in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia,
in October, ASEAN Secretary-General Ajit Singh, who is visiting
Brazil, was quoted today by the press.
</P>
<P>
