Foreign Minister Luiz Lampreia had discussed measures to increase
trade exchanges between the seven-member ASEAN and four-nation
Mercosur, the largest trade bloc in South America.
</P>
<P>
The council will help member countries, identify and try to
find solutions to problems in inter-regional trade, Singh said.
</P>
<P>
"We did not discuss specific themes. We spoke, in general
terms, about the way to advance toward a commercial agreement
between the two blocs," said Singh. 
