<HEADLINE> U.S. Asked to Respect for Human Rights of Mexicans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Mexico will recur to all the
arguments of diplomacy to reclaim and demand respect to the human
and labor rights of Mexicans, President Ernesto Zedillo said today.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican president made the statement three days after the
new U.S. illegal immigration law went in force in the United
States.
</P>
<P>
He said Mexicans feel hurt and offended when their brothers and
sisters who cross the border to go to the United States are object
of ill-treatment, abuse, and insult, and violations to their
fundamental human rights.
</P>
<P>
Zedillo said that as president of the republic, he will never
try to dictate laws to other countries, because he will never
accept that foreign powers will come to Mexico to dictate laws to
the Mexicans. 
</P>
