<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Vessel Ready for Evacuation from Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Navy helicopter warship USS
Nassau, with 1,338 marines aboard, is in position off the coast of
Zaire, ready to assist in an evacuation of Americans from Zaire,
if necessary, Pentagon said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"We're there in case an evacuation is necessary," Pentagon
spokesman Ken Bacon told reporters at a briefing. "The USS Nassau
is currently on station about 220 miles off the coast of Africa,
about the confluence of Congo, Zaire and Angola."
</P>
<P>
Defense officials said there are believed to be more than 500
Americans in Zaire, including some 470 private citizens.
</P>
<P>
Bacon stressed there had been no request from the U.S. Embassy
in the capital of Kinshasa for a rescue operation.
</P>
<P>
However, the USS Nassau, an amphibious vessel, could move
farther in if the situation warrants, he added.
</P>
<P>
The Army forces were also sent into the region several weeks
ago to establish communications and basic security in the event an
evacuation was ordered by vessel, helicopter or military transport
plane. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
