<HEADLINE> Greek Consulate in Southern Albania Attacked Once Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Greek consulate in Gjirokaster,
southern Albania, was attacked once again by armed insurgents
today, according to a report released by the semi-official Athens
News Agency (ANA).
</P>
<P>
A number of men, armed with guns and grenades, managed to
disarm the consulate's police guards and enter the building,
demanding consular staff issue them visas, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Threats to use the grenades and to shoot forced police to clear
the surrounding area of the thousands of Albanians who had
gathered to apply for visas.
</P>
<P>
The consulate was forced to close shortly afterwards.
</P>
<P>
The incident came almost a week after a similar incident in
which armed men broke through the main entrance, firing tear gas
cannisters and shots into the crowded building.
</P>
<P>
The Greek consulate reopened only after local authorities
promised that the building would be guarded. 
</P>
