<HEADLINE> Greek National Bank to Issue Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The National Bank of Greece, the
largest in the country, will issue a long-term subordinated debt
bond loan of 150-200 million U.S. dollars in the international
markets.
</P>
<P>
